---
import { icon } from './icons';
---

<section class="bet">
  <div class="atlas-inner grid">
    <div class="col-left">
      <p class="eyebrow">THE BET</p>
      <h2>Own the agents. Rent the model.</h2>
      <p class="lead">
        Serious enterprises never put core banking, ERP, or the trade engine on someone else's
        SaaS — they build the core in-house and wire in cloud products at the edges. The agent
        layer is becoming exactly that kind of core system: it orchestrates your proprietary
        business logic and sits between you and your users.
      </p>
      <p class="lead muted">
        The model is a commodity — rent it, self-host an open one, or grow your own. The
        <span class="hl">loop</span> — user ↔ agent ↔ your logic — you keep. That's the IP no
        serious enterprise cedes to a vendor's cloud.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="cards">
      <article class="card rent">
        <div class="c-head">
          <span class="c-icon red" set:html={icon('close', 15)} />
          <span class="c-title">Rent the agents</span>
        </div>
        <div class="c-body">
          <span>Your logic and your users routed through a vendor's cloud control plane.</span>
          <span>Telemetry funnels back into <em>their</em> platform.</span>
          <span>Lock-in decided before anyone signs.</span>
        </div>
      </article>
      <article class="card own">
        <div class="c-head">
          <span class="c-icon blue" set:html={icon('check', 15)} />
          <span class="c-title">Own them, in your cluster</span>
        </div>
        <div class="c-body">
          <span>Runs on the stack you already operate — K8s, OCI, OTel, Postgres.</span>
          <span>Open source — pull it, read it, run it, before you sign.</span>
          <span>Your agents and telemetry stay <em class="acc">yours</em>.</span>
        </div>
      </article>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .bet {
    padding: 76px 30px 84px;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--hairline);
    background: var(--surface-1);
  }
  .grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 0.92fr 1.08fr;
    gap: 56px;
    align-items: center;
  }
  .eyebrow {
    margin: 0 0 14px;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: 12px;
    letter-spacing: 0.14em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--starlight);
  }
  h2 {
    margin: 0 0 16px;
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: 36px;
    line-height: 1.12;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    color: var(--star-100);
  }
  .lead {
    margin: 0 0 20px;
    max-width: 460px;
    font-size: 16px;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--star-600);
  }
  .lead.muted {
    margin-bottom: 0;
    color: var(--star-500);
  }
  .hl {
    color: var(--star-300);
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .cards {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 14px;
  }
  .card {
    border: 1px solid var(--hairline);
    border-radius: var(--radius-card);
    background: var(--surface-card);
    padding: 24px 22px;
  }
  .card.own {
    border-color: var(--starlight-border);
    background: var(--grad-blue-wash);
  }
  .c-head {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 9px;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }
  .c-icon {
    width: 26px;
    height: 26px;
    flex: none;
    display: grid;
    place-items: center;
    border-radius: 7px;
  }
  .c-icon.red {
    background: rgba(239, 68, 68, 0.1);
    color: var(--signal-red);
  }
  .c-icon.blue {
    background: var(--starlight-tint);
    color: var(--starlight);
  }
  .c-icon :global(svg) {
    display: block;
  }
  .c-title {
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: 15px;
    color: var(--star-200);
  }
  .card.own .c-title {
    color: var(--star-100);
  }
  .c-body {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 12px;
    font-size: 13px;
    line-height: 1.45;
    color: var(--star-600);
  }
  .card.own .c-body {
    color: var(--star-500);
  }
  .c-body em {
    font-style: normal;
    color: var(--star-400);
  }
  .c-body em.acc {
    color: var(--starlight);
    font-weight: 500;
  }
  @media (max-width: 880px) {
    .grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 36px;
    }
  }
  @media (max-width: 520px) {
    .cards {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
